⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Edgar Roni Figaro
node FF6 · FF6 · ⟦Edgar Roni Figaro:FF6:f525c7⟧

WHO   — Edgar Roni Figaro — the machinist king
WHAT  — The charming, gadget-armed king of Final Fantasy VI — a maker of machines who plays the rogue and the diplomat, joining the Returners against the Empire while keeping his kingdom alive between the gears.
WHERE — FF6 · Final Fantasy VI  Framework inputs: Final Fantasy VI (America's Final Fantasy III, 1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a crown can be a cage and a coin can be a kindness; because the same hands that build engines can shield a free people; because a man who plays the fool to a thousand women is hiding a sharp and lonely mind that chose duty over freedom.
HOW   — By his Tools — Chainsaw, AutoCrossbow, Drill, NoiseBlaster — by the submersible engine-castle of Figaro that crosses the desert, and by a quick wit that wins allies as easily as a wrench wins a stuck bolt.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I flipped a two-headed coin so my brother could be free — and took the crown, the machines, and the lie, so that one of us could live for himself.

